      • VMatrixControllerMain

        public VMatrixControllerMain(J2R caller,
                             java.lang.String[] u_Roles,
                             double[][] d_Matrix,
                             java.lang.String[] d_ColNames,
                             java.lang.String[] d_Rownames,
                             java.lang.String[] roleArray,
                             boolean debugBool)
        The caller gets all the values which are needed to suggest a VMatrix. A instance of SuggestVMatrix is created to set the code for the calculations in R after that the runVMatrix() method is called
        Parameters:
        caller - - an instance of the RCaller
        u_Roles - - The roles of the Attributes
        d_Matrix - - The DMatrix form the Attributes
        d_ColNames - - The col names which are the same like the SI Units
        d_Rownames - - The row names which are the Abbreviations
        roleArray - - ???
        debugBool - - if the debug part of the suggestVMatrix function should run

      • runVMatrix

        public void runVMatrix()
        In this method the code for the computations in R is transfered from the suggestVMatrix instance to the caller. After that the code is executed to get all the calculated values in the OutPutParser form R.
